_Objective:_ The primary objective of this study is to assess the significance of in-game behavior within the context of Kabaddi, a prominent sport originating in South Asia.

_Methods:_ To achieve this objective, we will closely examine the rules, court, and points accumulation in a Kabaddi match, as well as the individual player performance data. Our approach involves the quantification and analysis of this information to explore its potential applications, including performance enhancement for players and teams, and strategic development.

_Results:_ The findings from our analysis will shed light on the value of in-game behavior in Kabaddi, offering insights into player performance, team dynamics, and strategic opportunities.

_Conclusion:_ This research has the potential to make a meaningful contribution to the competitive landscape of Kabaddi by harnessing the insights gained from the quantification of in-game behavior.